        <num>CCRP 220</num>
        <heading>220.  Submission to arrest; use of force</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 220.  Submission to arrest; use of force
A person shall submit peaceably to a lawful arrest.  The person making a lawful arrest may use reasonable force to effect the arrest and detention, and also to overcome any resistance or threatened resistance of the person being arrested or detained.</p>
        </content>
